{{zh-forms|[[三更灯火五更鸡]]|[[三更]][[燈火]][[五更]][[雞]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
Literally: by candle-light at the third watch, up with the chickens at the fifth watch
===Idiom===
{{PAGENAME}} (''[[Pinyin]]'' sāngēng dēnghuǒ wŭgēng jī)
# to [[burn the midnight oil]], only to get up at the crack of dawn
# to work long hours
# to [[burn one's candle at both ends]]
#* ''2004'' 武少民 (Wu Shaomin), ''[http://www.people.com.cn/GB/jiaoyu/1055/2789198.html 来信选登:素质教育比不上高考升学率？]'' (Letters to the Editor: Quality education cannot compare to the rate at which students pass high school entrance exams?)
#: ''[[就是]][[這樣]][[的]][[一]][[道]][[檻]]，[[讓]][[眾多]][[的]][[學子]]“'''三更燈火五更雞'''”，[[讓]][[眾多]][[的]][[學校]][[加]][[課]][[補]][[課]][[取消]][[節]][[假日]].''
#: ''It's just this kind of threshold that causes many students to study '''late into the night, only to get up and go to class the next morning'''.  It also causes many schools to add extra classes, including make-up classes, and to cancel holidays and days off.''

